<p>Generalized coordinate 
 <bold>Q</bold> is the periodic function of the time t 
 <disp-formula id="FD59-micromachines-10-00181">
  <label>(58)</label>
  <math id="mm65">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mstyle mathvariant="bold" mathsize="normal">
      <mover accent="true">
       <mi>Q</mi>
       <mo stretchy="false">^</mo>
      </mover>
     </mstyle>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <mstyle mathvariant="bold" mathsize="normal">
      <mi mathvariant="bold-sans-serif">ξ</mi>
     </mstyle>
     <mi>sin</mi>
     <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
     <mi>ω</mi>
     <mi>t</mi>
     <mo>+</mo>
     <mi>φ</mi>
     <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula> where, ω is the natural frequency, φ is the phase, and ξ is the undetermined coefficient vector. Taking (58) into (56):
 <disp-formula id="FD60-micromachines-10-00181">
  <label>(59)</label>
  <math id="mm66">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mstyle mathvariant="bold" mathsize="normal">
      <mi>K</mi>
      <mi mathvariant="bold-sans-serif">ξ</mi>
     </mstyle>
     <mo>−</mo>
     <msup>
      <mi>ω</mi>
      <mn>2</mn>
     </msup>
     <mstyle mathvariant="bold" mathsize="normal">
      <mi>M</mi>
      <mi mathvariant="bold-sans-serif">ξ</mi>
     </mstyle>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <mn>0</mn>
     <mo>⇒</mo>
     <msup>
      <mstyle mathvariant="bold" mathsize="normal">
       <mi>M</mi>
      </mstyle>
      <mrow>
       <mo>−</mo>
       <mn>1</mn>
      </mrow>
     </msup>
     <mstyle mathvariant="bold" mathsize="normal">
      <mi>K</mi>
      <mi mathvariant="bold-sans-serif">ξ</mi>
     </mstyle>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <msup>
      <mi>ω</mi>
      <mn>2</mn>
     </msup>
     <mstyle mathvariant="bold" mathsize="normal">
      <mi mathvariant="bold-sans-serif">ξ</mi>
     </mstyle>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula>
</p>
